---

### DriftWatch statistics


Shows:

- current phase / tier  
- open drift count  
- last drift timestamp  
- drift events per day (last 14 days)

---

## What does “0 open drift” mean?

It means:

> There are **no unacknowledged drift events right now**.

It does **not** mean no drift has ever occurred — acknowledged drift remains part of the audit trail.

---

## Exit Codes

| Code | Meaning |
|------|--------|
| 0 | success |
| 2 | nothing found |
| 10 | ledger unavailable |

---

## Philosophy

DriftWatch exists to make **authority erosion observable**.

It does not correct behavior.  
It preserves memory.  
Humans remain accountable.
